com.efnilite.connotations.example

Class ExampleCommands

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.efnilite.connotations.example.ExampleCommands
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Commandable

    public class ExampleCommands
extends java.lang.Object
implements Commandable
    An example class for commands.

    Steps to register your own command class:

    1 - Create a new Class

    2 - Make it implement Commandable

    3 - Create a method that has the Command

    Note: the method name is the name of the command! If a method is named 'hello' it will register the command hello.

    Note: the method must have the args as CommandSender and String[]. Variable name does not matter.
